                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Late 18th-century script.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red, crimson.</seg>
                        <desc>Fine and careful.</desc>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; 1st, 3rd and 5th
                           line of the incipit of each text (occasionally in both columns); Ethiopic
                           numerals and the first two lines of the chapters; first two lines of the
                           final prayers of each text and the supplication prayers of  <ref  target="ms_i1.7"/>;
                           names of the days of the week written in the upper margin throughout the
                           manuscript, and the name “Fäläskinos” (fols. 146v, 147r, 149r, 151r); the word
                           mǝʾǝraf “chapter”; elements of the punctuation signs and Ethiopic
                           numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
